
-->Most virtual machines are hosted on, or works inside of, a physical machine. For virtual machine to work, the hosted physical machine 		provides software called hypervisor.

-->A thin layer of software called a “hypervisor” decouples the virtual machines from the host and dynamically allocates computing resources to 	each virtual machine as needed.

-->Yes, They have different virtual IP addresses as each of the VM's have a virtual NIC which does hardware virtualization and uses the 		underlying Physical NIC to send packets.
